description:
The Justin Varnes Quartet plays tribute to the music of Clark Terry.

Your donation is greatly appreciated.  Go to thevelvetnote.com/donate

As with the entire Legends of Jazz series, Mr. Varnes will guide guests–in engaging, narrative form– through the life of this legendary trumpeter and jazz flugelhorn pioneer,  as well as the impact that his life influences had on his musical legacy.   In this show, audiences will find out about the extraordinary life, including his unusual singing style that he was famed for, and his hallmark achievement on NBC television.  It’s like taking in a concert and taking a jazz history class at the same time, and…, oh… they’ll also play their behinds off!
